{"schemaVersion":1,"bookId":"situational-15000","unitId":"scene-375","title":"神秘热带雨林","sectionId":"chapter-16","sectionTitle":"天文地理有规律","pageStart":1828,"pageEnd":1831,"extractionMethod":"text-layer","wordEntryCount":16,"duplicateEntryCount":17,"pages":[{"number":1828,"blocks":[{"type":"title","text":"375 神秘热带雨林"},{"type":"section","text":"Step1 场景词"},{"type":"entry","text":"jungle [ˈdʒʌŋɡl]","headword":"jungle"},{"type":"definition","text":"n.丛林"},{"type":"note","text":"◎in the jungle在丛林里"},{"type":"entry","text":"evergreen broad-leaf forest 常绿阔叶林","headword":"evergreen broad-leaf forest"}]},{"number":1829,"blocks":[{"type":"entry","text":"biological community 生物群落","headword":"biological community"},{"type":"entry","text":"animal paradise 动物乐土","headword":"animal paradise"},{"type":"entry","text":"explorer [ɪkˈsplɔːrə(r)]","headword":"explorer"},{"type":"definition","text":"n.探险家"},{"type":"entry","text":"rubber tree 橡胶树","headword":"rubber tree"}]},{"number":1830,"blocks":[{"type":"entry","text":"tree frog 树蛙","headword":"tree frog"},{"type":"entry","text":"boa [ˈbəʊə]","headword":"boa"},{"type":"definition","text":"n.蟒"},{"type":"note","text":"◎boa constrictor蟒蛇"},{"type":"entry","text":"leafcutter ant 切叶蚁","headword":"leafcutter ant"},{"type":"entry","text":"fire ant 火蚁","headword":"fire ant"},{"type":"entry","text":"cayman [ˈkeɪmən]","headword":"cayman"},{"type":"definition","text":"n.（南美的）短吻鳄"},{"type":"entry","text":"jaguar [ˈdʒæɡjuə(r)]","headword":"jaguar"},{"type":"definition","text":"n.美洲豹"},{"type":"entry","text":"candiru [ˌkændɪˈruː]","headword":"candiru"}]},{"number":1831,"blocks":[{"type":"definition","text":"n.寄生鲇；牙签鱼"},{"type":"entry","text":"conventional rain 对流雨","headword":"conventional rain"},{"type":"entry","text":"illegal logging 非法采伐","headword":"illegal logging"},{"type":"section","text":"Step2 学以致用"},{"type":"entry","text":"The Destruction of the Rain Forest热带雨林的破坏","headword":"The Destruction of the Rain Forest"},{"type":"text","text":"The recent steady decline in the destruction of the world's biggest rain"},{"type":"text","text":"forest has been reversed. Between July 2011 and August 2012,"},{"type":"text","text":"deforestation in the Amazon was at its lowest level since record began.But"},{"type":"text","text":"new figures show that in the last 12 months, it has jumped by 28%. Just"},{"type":"text","text":"over two and a half thousand square miles or almost six thousand square"},{"type":"text","text":"kilometres of forest was destroyed in the last year, the vast majority to"},{"type":"text","text":"make way for cattle ranching with substantial areas also taken over by soya"},{"type":"text","text":"production."},{"type":"text","text":"世界最大热带雨林的砍伐率持续稳定的下降趋势出现逆转。2011"},{"type":"text","text":"年7月到2012年8月间，亚马逊地区的森林砍伐率达到了有史以来最"},{"type":"text","text":"低。但新数据显示，在过去的12个月中，砍伐率猛增了28%。在过去"},{"type":"text","text":"的一年里，2500多平方英里（近6000平方公里）的森林遭到了破坏。"},{"type":"text","text":"大部分的破坏主要是为了建造畜牧场，还有大片区域被砍伐，用作大"},{"type":"text","text":"豆生产区。"}]}]}